      "body": "> Are there obvious alternatives like BitBucket or GitLab that can take over the CI and won't fail under similar pressure? Or are you thinking we self host a GitGogs?\n\nThe original post says:\n> self-hosting forgejo or using a commercial instance of it is easy enough. If anything moving off is helping reduce their increasing load.\n\nFrom what I've read, Gogs was sort the OG, Gitea forked Gogs, then Gitea owner pissed off the community with commercial decisions, then that forked to be forgejo.  Forgejo _seems_ like a legit project though and also supports a lot of open protocols such as Activity Pub and gasp RSS.  Moving to a project that supports RSS seems reason enough.\n",
